                    },
                    "body": "Scheduling for next minor release.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-22T11:55:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-22T11:55:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28134",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=amnuts",
                        "name": "amnuts",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Collington",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Doesn't seem that the solution to this was put in to a minor release since Matthew's comment in April, as looking at version 1.7.2 now the problem of having no 'for' attribute in the labels still exists.  Random IDs are generated, but then only used within the input tag itself.\n\nI'd suggest simply updating FormRadio.php so that the line:\n\n    $radio = '<label'\n\nbecomes:\n\n    $radio = '<label for=\"' . $optId . '\"'\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=amnuts",
                        "name": "amnuts",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Collington",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-13T03:18:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-13T03:18:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28394",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=amnuts",
                        "name": "amnuts",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Collington",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Patch file for the update.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=amnuts",
                        "name": "amnuts",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Collington",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-22T03:29:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-22T03:29:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35229",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This has been resolved at some point in the past; please see Zend_View_Helper_FormRadioTest::testRadioLabelContainsForAttributeTag(), as well as line 161 of the FormRadio view helper, which reads:\r\n{code}\r\n. $this->_htmlAttribs($label_attribs) . ' for=\"' . $optId . '\">'\r\n{code}\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-15T08:15:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-15T08:15:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38384",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=duael",
                        "name": "duael",
                        "displayName": "Edouard Cunibil",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I found a solution by redefining \"Label\" decorator on these fields !\r\n\r\nYou have to pass the \"disableFor\" option to the decorator. It will remove the \"for\" attribute of the main \"label\" tag but not from the checkboxes' ones.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=duael",
                        "name": "duael",
                        "displayName": "Edouard Cunibil",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-10T03:43:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-10T03:43:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39817",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Current trunk validates fine with\r\n{code}\r\n$form = new Zend_Form();\r\n$form->addElement('Radio', 'Woo', array('MultiOptions' => array('foo','bar','baz')));\r\n$form->addElement('Select', 'Zaa', array('MultiOptions' => array('foo','bar','baz')));\r\n$form->addElement('Multiselect', 'Qua', array('MultiOptions' => array('foo','bar','baz')));\r\n$form->addElement('MultiCheckbox', 'Qui', array('MultiOptions' => array('foo','bar','baz')));\r\n$form->addElement('submit','submit');\r\ndie($form->render());\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alab",
                        "name": "alab",
                        "displayName": "Christian Albrecht",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-05T07:07:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-05T07:07:34.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
